    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Our Story</h2>
      <p>Cosmic Captures began as a personal project to document the beauty of the night sky. What started as a hobby quickly evolved into a passion for capturing the most stunning astronomical objects visible from Earth.</p>
      <p>Each image in our gallery represents hours of planning, setup, exposure, and post-processing work. We travel to dark sky locations around the world to get the clearest possible views of celestial objects.</p>
      <p>Our mission is to share the wonders of the universe with everyone and inspire more people to look up at the night sky with curiosity and wonder.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Our Equipment</h2>
      <ul class="equipment-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-camera"></i> <strong>Primary Camera:</strong> Modified Canon EOS Ra (Astro-specialized)</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-telescope"></i> <strong>Main Telescope:</strong> Celestron EdgeHD 11" with 0.7x reducer</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-rocket"></i> <strong>Mount:</strong> Sky-Watcher EQ8-Rh Pro Equatorial Mount</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-filter"></i> <strong>Filters:</strong> Astronomik CLS-CCD, Ha 12nm, OIII 12nm, SII 12nm</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-laptop-code"></i> <strong>Software:</strong> PixInsight, Adobe Photoshop, Sequence Generator Pro</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-satellite-dish"></i> <strong>Guiding:</strong> ZWO ASI290MM Mini with 60mm guide scope</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Image Processing</h2>
      <p>Each image in our gallery is presented in two formats:</p>
      <p><strong>Raw:</strong> The initial stacked image with minimal processing, showing the data as captured by the camera.</p>
      <p><strong>Processed:</strong> The final image after careful processing to bring out details, colors, and contrast while maintaining scientific accuracy.</p>
      <p>Our processing workflow typically includes calibration, stacking, noise reduction, color calibration, and careful enhancement of details without introducing artifacts or false colors.</p>
    </section>
